WEBVTT

00:01.067 --> 00:02.669
LINDSAY: <i>Previously</i>
<i>on "The Practice"...</i>

00:02.703 --> 00:03.737
I'm on call

00:03.770 --> 00:05.238
for my rape crisis
center today.

00:05.271 --> 00:06.471
Is that going
to be okay?

00:06.507 --> 00:08.074
I thought you were
just in training.

00:08.108 --> 00:09.643
I thought you were
volunteering nights.

00:09.676 --> 00:10.711
I finished training
this weekend,

00:10.744 --> 00:12.345
and I am
volunteering nights.

00:12.378 --> 00:15.415
Can I get you anything --
a blanket, maybe?

00:15.448 --> 00:17.350
No! Aah!

00:17.383 --> 00:20.486
She panicked.
She totally panicked.

00:20.521 --> 00:22.288
Well, you won't
do that next time.

00:22.322 --> 00:24.290
There's not going
to be a next time.

00:24.324 --> 00:25.425
Maddie.

00:25.458 --> 00:27.293
Are you Lucy?

00:27.327 --> 00:28.328
Yeah.

00:30.697 --> 00:32.298
Thank you.

00:32.332 --> 00:34.367
Sure.

00:34.400 --> 00:37.270
I'm going to see you
at the clinic, right?

00:37.303 --> 00:39.540
I'll be there.

00:39.573 --> 00:42.175
Harland Bassett
to see Eugene Young.

00:42.208 --> 00:43.443
Is he available?

00:43.476 --> 00:45.411
Um...

00:45.445 --> 00:48.549
Eugene.

00:48.582 --> 00:50.083
She's my niece,

00:50.116 --> 00:51.618
so naturally,
I have a vested interest,

00:51.652 --> 00:53.286
besides
her being innocent.

00:53.319 --> 00:55.188
Is it a burglary?

00:55.221 --> 00:57.223
No, no, no,
just shoplifting.

00:57.257 --> 00:59.793
It's a false I. D.,
Eugene.

00:59.826 --> 01:02.863
-Are you certain this is
the woman you saw?
-I am.

01:02.896 --> 01:05.230
-Positive?
-Yes.

01:05.265 --> 01:06.633
At this time,
I would ask

01:06.667 --> 01:08.702
that the real Emma Luger
please stand up.

01:08.735 --> 01:11.672
I will see counsel
in chambers.

01:11.705 --> 01:13.439
Both of you
are in contempt.

01:13.473 --> 01:15.108
I didn't know.

01:15.141 --> 01:16.677
I told you I would
hold you accountable.

01:16.710 --> 01:18.679
You're in contempt.

01:22.883 --> 01:24.384
Who's your D. A.?

01:24.417 --> 01:25.752
Helen Gamble.

01:25.786 --> 01:28.088
You know, I actually
really like working with her.

01:29.389 --> 01:31.792
Don't you have a kid
to go home to?

01:31.825 --> 01:34.227
I do, and I'm going.
How late are you going to be?

01:34.260 --> 01:36.296
Oh, not much longer.

01:36.329 --> 01:37.664
Richard.

01:40.834 --> 01:44.505
Guzman -- 18 months.

01:44.538 --> 01:48.241
That's the same offer
you made over the phone.

01:48.274 --> 01:51.512
I know. I came here
to make it in person.

01:51.545 --> 01:52.913
What's the matter?

01:52.946 --> 01:53.914
Nothing.

01:53.947 --> 01:56.583
I just think you should
take the deal on Guzman.

01:56.617 --> 01:59.753
The drugs weren't his.
I can't recommend him --

01:59.786 --> 02:01.888
He won't win this.

02:01.922 --> 02:05.291
You're acting a little odd.
Why have you come down here?

02:05.325 --> 02:08.261
I'm talking to you now
not just as a D. A., Lindsay,

02:08.294 --> 02:10.830
but one with whom your firm
has a relationship.

02:10.864 --> 02:12.799
Do your client
a very big favor

02:12.833 --> 02:14.835
and convince him
to take this deal.

02:16.436 --> 02:18.438
I'm gonna ask you
one more time.

02:18.471 --> 02:19.806
What is going on?

02:19.840 --> 02:21.875
I'm just here
to suggest very strongly

02:21.908 --> 02:23.610
that he take
the 18 months.

02:23.644 --> 02:25.178
That's all I will say.

02:26.379 --> 02:27.948
The offer is rejected.

02:27.981 --> 02:32.418
Linsay, please.

02:32.452 --> 02:33.754
Tell me more
than what you're telling me.

02:33.787 --> 02:36.489
I can't.

02:36.523 --> 02:38.525
The offer is rejected.

02:49.770 --> 02:52.773
