03:40.721 --> 03:42.956
18 months doesn't sound
like a terrible offer.

03:42.989 --> 03:45.291
He says
the drugs weren't his.

03:45.325 --> 03:47.460
Understood, but if your defense
is the police planted them,

03:47.493 --> 03:48.929
when he's got a prior --

03:48.962 --> 03:51.464
Well, first of all,
I think I can beat the search.

03:51.497 --> 03:53.333
What if you can't?
Will the deal still be there?

03:53.366 --> 03:54.801
I don't know.

03:54.835 --> 03:57.270
Take it.

03:57.303 --> 03:58.271
Take it.

03:58.304 --> 03:59.673
Take it.

03:59.706 --> 04:01.575
Eugene?

04:04.077 --> 04:06.747
I saw you, Eugene.
Very funny.

04:12.853 --> 04:15.421
After the detective,
I'll call you to the stand.

04:15.455 --> 04:16.857
You'll make the I. D.,

04:16.890 --> 04:18.858
and then I'll ask you
to describe the rape.

04:18.892 --> 04:20.060
Now, I'm going
to need you

04:20.093 --> 04:22.328
to be as detailed
as possible.

04:22.362 --> 04:24.998
Okay, Meredith?

04:25.031 --> 04:27.333
Meredith?

04:27.367 --> 04:29.636
Okay.

04:29.670 --> 04:31.037
Look, I know
this is rough,

04:31.071 --> 04:32.706
but I'll be there
with you.

04:32.739 --> 04:34.440
I'll walk you
through this.

04:34.474 --> 04:36.843
I don't understand why it's me
who has to go on trial.

04:36.877 --> 04:38.411
You won't be on trial.

04:38.444 --> 04:40.480
It's just going
to seem that way.

04:41.782 --> 04:43.884
I'll come get you
in a few minutes.

04:43.917 --> 04:45.519
Okay.

04:49.690 --> 04:51.725
Your parents
didn't fly in?

04:51.758 --> 04:54.728
I talked them
out of it.

04:56.496 --> 04:59.465
The truth is the less people
that know me in there,

04:59.499 --> 05:01.034
the better.

05:01.067 --> 05:04.605
Meredith, you don't have
any shame in this.

05:04.638 --> 05:06.372
I know, but that
defense attorney,

05:06.406 --> 05:08.474
he is going to blame me.
You said that yourself.

05:08.509 --> 05:11.344
I also said that
that's standard strategy

05:11.377 --> 05:12.746
in date rape cases.

05:12.779 --> 05:15.882
If you just go in there
and stay strong,

05:15.916 --> 05:19.352
stick to the truth,
you're going to be fine.

05:19.385 --> 05:21.755
Thank you for being here.

05:21.788 --> 05:24.825
I would have never made it
this far.

05:24.858 --> 05:27.894
Well, you have.

05:27.928 --> 05:30.931
There's just a little
further to go.

05:33.800 --> 05:34.968
The stuff wasn't mine.

05:35.001 --> 05:36.369
10 grams, Manny.

05:36.402 --> 05:38.071
You could be looking
at a lot of time.

05:38.104 --> 05:40.040
Look, if they're offering
18 months,

05:40.073 --> 05:42.475
that tells me the D.A.
knows this is weak.

05:42.509 --> 05:44.678
Or maybe he knows
the drugs were planted.

05:44.711 --> 05:47.614
I don't think he'd prosecute
if he thought that.

05:50.150 --> 05:54.387
Look...

05:54.420 --> 05:57.390
this D. A., he seems
to be suggesting

05:57.423 --> 06:00.026
that something else
could be in play here.

06:00.060 --> 06:02.495
Do you know
what that could be?

06:02.529 --> 06:04.464
No.

06:04.497 --> 06:05.799
Could he be bluffing,

06:05.832 --> 06:07.467
afraid he might lose
the suppression hearing?

06:07.501 --> 06:10.537
It's possible, but I didn't
get that feeling.

06:10.571 --> 06:12.839
Why not just try
with the motion to suppress?

06:12.873 --> 06:14.407
And if we lose --

06:14.440 --> 06:15.776
My concern is

06:15.809 --> 06:17.944
the state may pull the plea
if they win on that.

06:17.978 --> 06:22.148
The stuff wasn't mine.

06:22.182 --> 06:25.451
I'm not going
to cop to it.

06:27.754 --> 06:30.724
Let's try to suppress.
We'll go from there.

06:39.465 --> 06:40.567
Ms. Dole.

06:41.802 --> 06:43.469
Uh, look,

06:43.504 --> 06:45.839
I basically raised
my brother.

06:45.872 --> 06:47.874
He never knew
his father.

06:47.908 --> 06:51.011
Now, he's an honest kid,
and he's made mistakes,

06:51.044 --> 06:53.714
but he owns them
when he does.

06:53.747 --> 06:56.216
Look, what I'm trying
to say is

06:56.249 --> 06:58.985
if he says
the drugs weren't his,

06:59.019 --> 07:00.554
they weren't his.

07:00.587 --> 07:02.923
I'll do my best, Hector.

07:02.956 --> 07:07.460
Ms. Dole, look, I --
I've done okay for myself.

07:07.493 --> 07:10.997
I have the auto shop
and all, but...

07:11.031 --> 07:14.601
Manny -- he's good
at school, even.

07:14.635 --> 07:17.470
He's got a chance
at college.

07:17.504 --> 07:20.741
I'll help your brother
as best I can.

07:20.774 --> 07:22.442
Thank you.

07:24.244 --> 07:26.212
I developed the case.
I already settled out

07:26.246 --> 07:27.881
with the doctor.
I just need --

07:27.914 --> 07:28.949
For $45,000.

07:28.982 --> 07:31.785
13-year-old girl,
liver failure?

07:31.818 --> 07:33.486
$45,000 seems low.

07:33.520 --> 07:34.888
They needed the money.

07:34.921 --> 07:36.489
Plus, the drug company
is the deep pocket here.

07:36.523 --> 07:38.224
Well, have they
offered anything?

07:38.258 --> 07:40.226
Not yet,
but you know how this goes.

07:40.260 --> 07:42.629
Things get settled
on the courthouse steps.

07:42.663 --> 07:43.664
I expect an offer.

07:43.697 --> 07:46.533
Oh, you do.

07:46.567 --> 07:48.702
The girl got hurt bad,
Eugene, like you say,

07:48.735 --> 07:50.170
and these big
drug companies,

07:50.203 --> 07:52.138
they don't like
the publicity of trials.

07:52.172 --> 07:54.641
They don't like to set
a precedent of settling, either.

07:54.675 --> 07:58.044
Now, you said this drug comes
with a warning to doctors --

07:58.078 --> 08:00.246
"Not proven
to be safe and effective

08:00.280 --> 08:01.915
on children under 16."

08:01.948 --> 08:03.617
Saying "Not proven
to be safe"

08:03.650 --> 08:05.218
is different
from saying "Dangerous."

08:05.251 --> 08:07.654
I'm telling you, Eugene,
there's a case here.

08:07.688 --> 08:08.755
They'll settle this.

08:12.225 --> 08:13.794
Okay.

08:13.827 --> 08:15.962
And why do you need me?

08:15.996 --> 08:19.232
Well, my track record
in product liability cases --

08:19.265 --> 08:22.102
I don't think I exactly
put the fear of God in them.

08:22.135 --> 08:25.639
Now, your case
where you took on the EPA --

08:25.672 --> 08:26.940
A $30 million verdict.

08:26.973 --> 08:28.609
It was cut down.

08:28.642 --> 08:29.943
But you got the verdict.

08:29.976 --> 08:32.078
If I have you guys
on board as co-counsel,

08:32.111 --> 08:34.080
I know I can
chip the settlement up.

08:34.114 --> 08:36.182
I'll give you
a third of my contingency.

08:36.216 --> 08:37.851
Harland, I don't know.

08:37.884 --> 08:40.687
Please. These are
good people, Eugene.

08:40.721 --> 08:42.121
Yeah, but every time
I sign up with you,

08:42.155 --> 08:43.323
I end up
getting embarrassed.

08:43.356 --> 08:45.291
That's not going
to happen this time.

08:45.325 --> 08:46.927
I've worked hard here.

08:46.960 --> 08:48.595
I developed the file.

08:48.629 --> 08:50.664
I beat their motion
to dismiss.

08:50.697 --> 08:52.132
I got it to trial.

08:52.165 --> 08:54.735
I got it to trial.

08:54.768 --> 08:57.671
But you don't think
you can win at trial.

08:57.704 --> 09:00.774
That's why you're
so desperate to settle.

09:00.807 --> 09:04.077
I just want to be sure
they get something.

09:10.651 --> 09:14.287
We had been to a party
and he was walking me home.

09:14.320 --> 09:15.922
HELEN: The defendant?

09:15.956 --> 09:18.625
Yes.

09:18.659 --> 09:24.465
And we got
about halfway to my dorm

09:25.932 --> 09:27.233
when...

09:27.267 --> 09:29.335
When what, Meredith?

09:29.369 --> 09:31.972
Well, first he just
started saying

09:32.005 --> 09:34.340
that he was going
to come back to my room

09:34.374 --> 09:36.677
with me so that
we could fool around.

09:36.710 --> 09:39.379
What did you say
to that?

09:39.412 --> 09:41.381
I think
I laughed it off.

09:41.414 --> 09:43.850
I didn't want to be mean,

09:43.884 --> 09:45.719
so I didn't
really answer him.

09:45.752 --> 09:48.955
And then when we got
to my room,

09:48.989 --> 09:50.056
we went inside.

09:50.090 --> 09:51.692
You let him in?

09:51.725 --> 09:53.393
Yes.

09:53.426 --> 09:55.328
We were still talking,

09:55.361 --> 09:57.864
and I had some soda
in my refrigerator,

09:57.898 --> 10:00.366
so we had a drink.

10:00.400 --> 10:03.970
And then, suddenly,
he just grabbed me,

10:04.004 --> 10:06.072
and he tried
to kiss me.

10:06.106 --> 10:07.974
What did you do then?

10:08.008 --> 10:09.976
I pushed him off.

10:10.010 --> 10:11.978
We weren't even
on a date.

10:12.012 --> 10:14.948
He was just walking me home
from a party.

10:14.981 --> 10:17.851
And what happened after
you tried to push him off?

10:17.884 --> 10:19.853
I think I laughed again,

10:19.886 --> 10:21.187
I don't know,

10:21.221 --> 10:24.124
to make the situation
less awkward,

10:24.157 --> 10:28.394
but I told him,
"No. It's time to go."

10:28.428 --> 10:31.732
And he grabbed me again.

10:31.765 --> 10:34.034
After you said no?

10:34.067 --> 10:35.101
Yes.

10:35.135 --> 10:37.838
He pushed me
onto the floor.

10:37.871 --> 10:39.873
And then what, Meredith?

10:39.906 --> 10:42.809
He pulled up my skirt

10:42.843 --> 10:47.047
and...

10:47.080 --> 10:50.016
he pulled my panties down.

10:50.050 --> 10:51.885
What did you do?

10:51.918 --> 10:55.021
I tried
to fight him off,

10:55.055 --> 10:59.960
but he had my knees
pinned to the floor,

10:59.993 --> 11:03.396
and I couldn't...

11:03.429 --> 11:07.901
and then he was, um...

11:07.934 --> 11:10.937
forcing himself
inside of me.

11:13.273 --> 11:15.308
And did you have intercourse?

11:15.341 --> 11:17.443
It wasn't intercourse.

11:17.477 --> 11:20.113
At anytime did you
consent to this?

11:20.146 --> 11:21.748
No.

11:23.416 --> 11:26.419
He was raping me.

11:35.161 --> 11:36.362
I was on night patrol

11:36.396 --> 11:37.831
when I saw the defendant
run the stop sign.

11:37.864 --> 11:39.099
I pulled him over.

11:39.132 --> 11:40.366
What happened next?

11:40.400 --> 11:41.968
As I approached
the defendant's vehicle,

11:42.002 --> 11:43.036
he made a furtive gesture.

11:43.069 --> 11:45.305
What exactly did he do?

11:45.338 --> 11:46.807
He reached
under the seat

11:46.840 --> 11:47.841
as if he was going
for a weapon.

11:47.874 --> 11:48.909
And what did you do,
officer?

11:48.942 --> 11:50.110
Fearing for my safety,

11:50.143 --> 11:51.444
I pulled out
my service revolver

11:51.477 --> 11:53.446
and asked him
to step out of the vehicle.

11:53.479 --> 11:55.215
I then began
to search the vehicle

11:55.248 --> 11:56.249
for a possible weapon.

11:56.282 --> 11:57.918
Did you find any?

11:57.951 --> 11:59.385
No, but under
the driver's seat

11:59.419 --> 12:01.121
was a plastic baggie
containing what was

12:01.154 --> 12:03.023
later determined to be
10 grams of crack cocaine.

12:03.056 --> 12:04.490
I placed the defendant
under arrest

12:04.525 --> 12:06.092
and advised him
of his rights.

12:08.795 --> 12:10.263
You feared
for your safety?

12:10.296 --> 12:11.765
That's correct.

12:11.798 --> 12:13.534
After you got
the defendant out of his car,

12:13.567 --> 12:15.001
what did you do next?

12:15.035 --> 12:16.402
I searched for weapons.

12:16.436 --> 12:18.138
Did you call
for backup?

12:18.171 --> 12:19.540
No, I thought
I could handle it.

12:19.573 --> 12:21.274
Did you pat frisk?

12:21.307 --> 12:23.276
Actually, I thought
the weapon was in the vehicle.

12:23.309 --> 12:24.878
How about handcuffs?

12:24.911 --> 12:26.179
At that point, no.

12:26.212 --> 12:28.281
You were alone,
and you left my client

12:28.314 --> 12:30.183
unrestrained
and unsupervised?

12:30.216 --> 12:31.818
Like I said,
I thought I could--

12:31.852 --> 12:32.819
While you were
searching the vehicle,

12:32.853 --> 12:33.920
where was
the defendant standing?

12:33.954 --> 12:35.889
A few feet behind me,
I guess.

12:35.922 --> 12:37.257
You turned your back
on him

12:37.290 --> 12:38.892
while in fear
for your safety?

12:38.925 --> 12:40.994
Only for about
30 seconds or so.

12:41.027 --> 12:43.096
Your honor, we move to suppress
all evidence in this case.

12:43.129 --> 12:44.531
Officer Lemay's search here

12:44.565 --> 12:46.432
clearly does not fall
under the terry exception.

12:46.466 --> 12:48.234
He has failed to provide
any legal basis

12:48.268 --> 12:49.836
for a weapon search.

12:49.870 --> 12:52.005
The fact that the defendant
made a furtive gesture

12:52.038 --> 12:53.106
is not disputed here.

12:53.139 --> 12:54.274
If you consider

12:54.307 --> 12:56.109
the defendant's
suspicious behavior,

12:56.142 --> 12:57.978
the time of night,
the neighborhood --

12:58.011 --> 12:59.379
a reasonable
police officer

12:59.412 --> 13:01.114
would have feared
for his safety

13:01.147 --> 13:02.215
and searched the car.

13:02.248 --> 13:04.050
Perhaps,
but the fact remains,

13:04.084 --> 13:07.287
Officer Lemay failed to conduct
a simple pat frisk.

13:07.320 --> 13:10.991
That tells me he wasn't
threatened by this defendant,

13:11.024 --> 13:13.293
nor was he concerned
for his safety.

13:13.326 --> 13:15.829
I am finding the search
to be illegal.

13:15.862 --> 13:17.430
The charges are dismissed.

13:30.577 --> 13:33.079
Thank you.
Thank you so much.

13:33.113 --> 13:35.081
Manuel Guzman,
you're under arrest.

13:35.115 --> 13:36.883
-Get your hands off him!
-Step back, sir.

13:36.917 --> 13:38.885
What's going on here?

13:38.919 --> 13:40.153
Immigration, your honor.

13:40.186 --> 13:41.187
We're placing this man
under arrest.

13:41.221 --> 13:42.523
On what grounds?

13:42.556 --> 13:44.424
Violations of the Illegal
Immigration Reform

13:44.457 --> 13:46.059
and Immigrant
Responsibility act.

13:47.427 --> 13:48.595
What?

13:48.629 --> 13:50.931
WOMAN: What's happening?

13:55.969 --> 13:57.237
You're deporting him?

13:57.270 --> 13:59.305
Don't worry, Manny.
I'll take care of this.

13:59.339 --> 14:01.942
Don't say a word to anybody,
okay? Do not talk.

14:13.086 --> 14:14.254
Where to?

14:14.287 --> 14:17.457
I guess
the conference room.

14:17.490 --> 14:19.325
What's going on?

14:19.359 --> 14:21.394
Oh, uh, Harland Bassett.

14:21.427 --> 14:22.929
Yes, I know.
What's going on?

14:22.963 --> 14:24.497
Eugene and I have
a settlement conference.

14:24.531 --> 14:26.032
Here?

14:26.066 --> 14:28.569
Yes. Opposing counsel wanted
to have it at my office,

14:28.602 --> 14:31.204
I think because they suspect
I don't have one.

14:31.237 --> 14:32.606
Harland --

14:32.639 --> 14:34.274
I can't have our office
cluttered up --

14:34.307 --> 14:36.376
I will make it
all neat, I swear.

14:38.178 --> 14:39.646
Eugene.

14:44.651 --> 14:48.555
I didn't know he was going
to bring the stuff here.

14:48.589 --> 14:51.391
What's this case,
and what's our involvement?

14:51.424 --> 14:53.193
Product liability
against a drug company

14:53.226 --> 14:55.028
that injured a little girl.
