to the Rape Crisis Center

26:19.913 --> 26:21.648
because she knew
she had been raped.

26:21.682 --> 26:23.617
Have you ever tried
to convince someone

26:23.650 --> 26:25.385
to press charges when
they hadn't been raped?

26:25.418 --> 26:27.353
No.

26:27.387 --> 26:28.955
According
to her testimony,

26:28.989 --> 26:30.090
Meredith decided
to press charges

26:30.123 --> 26:32.158
only after
talking to you.

26:32.192 --> 26:34.160
We talked
about the legal definition,

26:34.194 --> 26:35.762
and after
hearing the facts,

26:35.796 --> 26:37.764
I told her she should
speak to the police.

26:37.798 --> 26:40.033
So you gave her
the legal definition.

26:40.066 --> 26:41.034
Yes.

26:41.067 --> 26:42.636
Are you a lawyer?

26:42.669 --> 26:44.771
No, sir, I'm not.

26:44.805 --> 26:46.206
But you know enough
about the law

26:46.239 --> 26:47.407
to advise her
to call the police?

26:47.440 --> 26:49.910
Enough to give her
that option, yes.

26:49.943 --> 26:52.345
Who called the police --
You or Ms. Danzer?

26:52.378 --> 26:55.015
Actually, I did.
She was emotionally dis--

26:55.048 --> 26:56.316
You did.

26:56.349 --> 26:59.385
And you told the police
that she'd been raped?

26:59.419 --> 27:01.187
